<%= content_for(:title) do %>
  Flood risk activity exemption successfully registered
<% end %>

<%= content_for(:heading) do %>
  We’ve registered your exemption
<% end %>

<p class="panel">
  Your reference is: <%= @presenter.reference_number %>
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">Exemption registered:</h2>
<p>
  <%= @presenter.exemption_title %> <%= @presenter.exemption_code %><br />
  at grid reference <%= @presenter.grid_reference %>.
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">Things you need to do before you start work</h2>

<% if @presenter.asset? %>
<p>
  When we checked the location we found flood defences, river control works or culverts within 1 kilometre. Some of the conditions of your exemption refer to these. You should check to make sure you can meet the conditions.
</p>
<% end %>

<p>
  You should re-check the conditions of your exemptions in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/environmental-permitting-regulations-exempt-flood-risk-activities">flood risk activities guidance</a>
</p>


<% if @presenter.salmonid? %>
<h2 class="border-top">The location is on a river where salmon are protected</h2>
<p>
  This means you cannot do any work between 1 October and 14 March each year. If you need to work during this period, you must apply for a permit.
</p>
<% end %>

<h2 class="border-top">Date of registration</h2>

<p>
  <%= @presenter.reg_date %>
</p>

<p>
  Exemptions don’t expire except for dredging FRA23 which expires 3 years after the registration date and dredging FRA24 which expires 1 year after the registration date.
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">Responsible for activity (the ‘operator’)</h2>
<p>
  <%= @presenter.full_name %><br />
  <%= @presenter.primary_address %>
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">Who we will contact</h2>
<p>
  <%=  @presenter.name %>, <%=  @presenter.position %><br />
  Tel: <%=  @presenter.telephone_number %><br />
  <%=  @presenter.email_address %>
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">Your responsibilities</h2>
<p>
  The organisation or individual responsible must keep to the description and conditions for the exemption(s). We can prosecute them if they don’t do this.
</p>

<h2 class="border-top">If your activity changes</h2>
<p>
  If the location changes, you will need to register a new exemption.
</p>
<p>
  If the activity or the way you are doing the work changes, you will need to check if it is still exempt.
</p>
